        </div>


<p>Parse file containing an XML document, SAX style.</p><p>Wrapper for a call to the XML parser <a href="xmerl_scan.html"><code class="inline">xmerl_scan</code></a> with
a <a href="xmerl_scan.html#t:option_list/0"><code class="inline">hook_fun</code></a> for
using Xmerl export functionality directly after an entity is parsed.</p>
  </section>
</section>
<section class="detail" id="stream/2">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#stream/2" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">




              <h1 class="signature" translate="no">stream(Fname, Options)<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">Result</span></h1>





          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/xmerl/src/xmerl_eventp.erl#L109" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">


        <div class="specs">
          <h4 class="specs-title">Types</h4>

            <pre translate="no">Fname = <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:string/0">string</a>()</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Options = <a href="#t:option_list/0">option_list</a>()</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Result = {<a href="#t:xmlElement/0">xmlElement</a>(), <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:list/0">list</a>()} | {error, Reason}</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Reason = <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:term/0">term</a>()</pre>

        </div>


<p>Parse file containing an XML document as a stream, DOM style.</p><p>Wrapper for a call to the XML parser <a href="xmerl_scan.html"><code class="inline">xmerl_scan</code></a> with
a <a href="xmerl_scan.html#t:option_list/0"><code class="inline">continuation_fun</code></a> for handling
streams of XML data. Note that the <code class="inline">continuation_fun</code>, <code class="inline">acc_fun</code>,
<code class="inline">fetch_fun</code>, <code class="inline">rules</code> and <code class="inline">close_fun</code> options cannot be user defined
using this parser.</p>
  </section>
</section>
